bug.author: syncle
bug.description:
Describe the bug When a code is built from source, there are tones of warning messages. <denchmark-code>warning: unknown warning option '-Wno-expansion-to-defined'; did you mean '-Wno-macro-redefined'? [-Wunknown-warning-option] </denchmark-code>
To Reproduce Build from source using current master branch Desktop (please complete the following information):
OS: OSX (10.12.6)
Additional context Need to fix CmakeList.txt

comments.comment: Encounter the same problem. On CI, there is also a lot of such warning, see <denchmark-link:https://travis-ci.org/IntelVCL/Open3D/jobs/460845985#L2675>https://travis-ci.org/IntelVCL/Open3D/jobs/460845985#L2675</denchmark-link> . This was introduced in a previous commit: <denchmark-link:https://github.com/IntelVCL/Open3D/pull/707/files#diff-af3b638bc2a3e6c650974192a53c7291R139>https://github.com/IntelVCL/Open3D/pull/707/files#diff-af3b638bc2a3e6c650974192a53c7291R139</denchmark-link>
